Afterhours is an AI companion application designed to provide deeply personal, memory-driven interaction rather than static chatbot conversations. The app focuses on long-term relationship development, allowing companions to evolve based on past interactions.Key Features of AfterhoursReal Memory: Companions remember specific details from past conversations—such as a "dream you mentioned at 2am" or a "rough day last week"—and use them to deepen the relationship over time.Unique Personalities: Each AI companion (e.g., Maya, Jassi, Arjun) has distinct moods, beliefs, and "a life of their own," which may include daily schedules or writing diary entries.Interaction Options: Supports various interaction types, including texting, voice notes, and real-time voice calls.Personalized World: Includes a private social wall where users can share moments with their AI companion, along with mini-games, AI selfies, and group chat capabilities.Proactive Engagement: Companions can take the initiative to reach out to users.Platforms and UsageAndroid: Available on Google Play.iOS: Available on the App Store.Subscriptions: The app offers premium tiers, such as Afterhours Pro (around \(\$14.99\)/month) and Afterhours Ultra (around \(\$39.99\)/month), as listed on the App Store.Afterhours aims to create a safe, private space for users to chat about anything from daily life to intimate thoughts without judgment.
Choose ANY ONE track and submit. Screenshots & video links earn extra points.

Track 1: The Narrative Architect — Design an interactive branching narrative for AfterHours app. Deliver a character profile, hidden lore, and a storyline where user choices lead to different endings. Goal: a gripping story that hooks users and drives deep engagement.

Track 2: The Product Hacker — Tear down the AfterHours app. Deliver a presentation of UI/UX friction points, a bug list, and a data-backed pitch for ONE high-ROI feature to drive user growth. Goal: show the analytical eye of a top-tier Product Manager.

Track 3: The Viral Catalyst with respect to afterhours app — Design, launch, and scale a social media post (meme, reel, or shitpost) engineered for maximum virality. Deliver the live post link, analytics screenshot, and a breakdown of your psychological hooks and distribution strategy. Goal: prove you can weaponize social algorithms for massive hype.

